    <div class="full-title with-title-branding">
      <div class="title-branding"><a href="/taxonomy/term/868"><img src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/sight-and-sound-logo-280x69.png?itok=AEegRSbk" alt="" /></a></div>
  
  <h1>
          The Film Book poll    
    
      </h1>

  
  
        <div class="copy">
              <div class="intro"><p>Which are the most inspirational five books about film ever written? This was the question we asked 51 leading critics and writers and the results may surprise you&#8230;</p>
<p>Sight <span class="amp">&amp;</span> Sound reviews the latest film books every month. </p>
<p>☞ </p>
</div>
            
      
      
      
          </div>
  </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block">
      
  <div class="content">
    <div class="small-12 large-12 columns solo">
  
  
  
  </div>


<div class="clear"></div>
  </div>
</div>
      
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Content row -->
  <div id="main-content" class="row layout-box">

          <div id="region-content-left-1" class="large-8 small-12 columns left layout-item layout-item-first">
        <div class="block">
      
  <div class="content">
    <div class="small-12 large-12 columns solo">
  
  
  
      <div class="wysiwyg"><p><div class="image full">
  <img class="lazy lazy-hidden" data-aspect-ratio="0.9860788863109" data-src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/full/public/image/sight-sound-film-books-poll-intro-pic-by-anthony-oliver-crop.jpg?itok=8JbWj4g9" alt="" title="" /><noscript><img  data-aspect-ratio="0.9860788863109" src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/full/public/image/sight-sound-film-books-poll-intro-pic-by-anthony-oliver-crop.jpg?itok=8JbWj4g9" alt="" title="" /></noscript>      <div class="legend">
    <p>          <span class="copy">Credit: Anthony Oliver at <a href="http://www.aoimages.com">www.aoimages.com</a></span>
        </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</p>
</div>
  </div>


<div class="clear with-padding"></div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block">
      
  <div class="content">
    

                    <div class="primary box">

                                      <ul class="equalise xsmall-block-grid-1 small-block-grid-2 large-block-grid-3 with-bottom-margin">
                          <li>

                                                                    <a class="img " href="/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/polls-surveys/film-book-poll/introduction"><img class="full" src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/news/hitchcock-alfred-reville-alma-002-tea-in-study-00m-iw5_1000x750.jpg?itok=LFTy8qPS" alt="Print the legend: introducing the Film Book Poll" /></a>
                
                
                                  <p class='h5'><a href="/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/polls-surveys/film-book-poll/introduction">Print the legend: introducing the Film Book Poll</a></p>
                  <p>Which are the best five books about film ever written? Revealing his ideal film bookshelf, Nick James introduces our special poll.
                    <br /><span class='date'>Monday 3 May 2010</span>                                      </p>
                                  
              </li>
                          <li>

                                                                    <a class="img " href="/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/polls-surveys/film-book-poll/top-five"><img class="full" src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/news/sight-sound-film-book-poll-six-readers-in-cinema_1000x750.jpg?itok=7ce3WkTX" alt="Sight & Sound’s top five film books" /></a>
                
                
                                  <p class='h5'><a href="/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/polls-surveys/film-book-poll/top-five">Sight & Sound’s top five film books</a></p>
                  <p>Which are the best five books about film ever written? This was the question Sight &amp; Sound asked 51 leading critics and writers – and a clear-cut top five emerged…
                    <br /><span class='date'>Monday 3 May 2010</span>                                      </p>
                                  
              </li>
                          <li>

                                                                    <a class="img " href="/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/polls-surveys/film-book-poll/complete"><img class="full" src="https://www2.bfi.org.uk/sites/bfi.org.uk/files/styles/16x9_small/public/news/melville-jean-pierre-001-reading-magazine-00m-vir_1000x750.jpg?itok=FLoVsHhu" alt="The best film books, by 51 critics" /></a>
                
                
                                  <p class='h5'><a href="/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/polls-surveys/film-book-poll/complete">The best film books, by 51 critics</a></p>
                  <p>Which are the most inspirational five books about film ever written? This was the question we asked 51 leading critics and writers, and their answers are printed here in full.
                    <br /><span class='date'>Thursday 3 June 2010</span>                                      </p>
                                  
              </li>
                      </ul>
          <div class="clear"></div>
        </div>

      </div>
</div>
<div class="block">
      
  <div class="content">
    <div class="small-12 large-12 columns solo">
  
  
  
      <div class="wysiwyg"><p> </p>
<p>Sight <span class="amp">&amp;</span> Sound was supporting the Kraszna-Krausz Foundation’s <a href="http://www.kraszna-krausz.org.uk">And/or Book Awards</a>, the UK’s leading prizes for books published in the fields of photography and the moving image (including film, television and new media), which in 2010 were celebrating their 25th anniversary. The 2010 winners were Edward Burtynsky’s Oil (Steidl) and Robert Robertson’s Eisenstein and the Audiovisual (I. B. Tauris).</p>
</div>
  </div>


